		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Gordian Knot</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For other uses, see <a href="/wiki/Gordian_Knot_(disambiguation)" title="Gordian Knot (disambiguation)">Gordian Knot (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Alexander_cuts_the_Gordian_Knot.jpg" class="image" title="Alexander cuts the Gordian Knot, by Jean-Simon Berthélemy (1743–1811)"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/Alexander_cuts_the_Gordian_Knot.jpg/300px-Alexander_cuts_the_Gordian_Knot.jpg" width="300" height="232" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Alexander_cuts_the_Gordian_Knot.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<i>Alexander cuts the Gordian Knot</i>, by <a href="/wiki/Jean-Simon_Berth%C3%A9lemy" title="Jean-Simon Berthélemy">Jean-Simon Berthélemy</a> (1743–1811)</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <b>Gordian Knot</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Legend" title="Legend">legend</a> associated with <a href="/wiki/Alexander_the_Great" title="Alexander the Great">Alexander the Great</a>. It is often used as a <a href="/wiki/Metaphor" title="Metaphor">metaphor</a> for an intractable problem, solved by a bold stroke ("cutting the Gordian knot"):</p>
<blockquote>
<p>"Turn him to any cause of policy,<br />
The Gordian Knot of it he will unloose,<br />
Familiar as his garter" (<a href="/wiki/Shakespeare" title="Shakespeare" class="mw-redirect">Shakespeare</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Henry_V_(play)" title="Henry V (play)">Henry V</a></i>, Act 1 Scene 1. 45-47)</p>
</blockquote>
